func isDialError(err error) bool {

										

										
										

											133
											
        // Unwrap common network errors

										

										
										

											134
											
        var opErr *net.OpError

										

										
										

											135
											
        if errors.As(err, &opErr) {

										

										
										

											136
											
                // Check for syscall-level connection refused / network unreachable

										

										
										

											137
											
                if opErr.Err == syscall.ECONNREFUSED || opErr.Err == syscall.ENETUNREACH || opErr.Err == syscall.EHOSTUNREACH {

										

										
										

											138
											
                        return true

										

										
										

											139
											
                }

										

										
										

											140
											
                // Sometimes nested errors wrap syscall.Errno

										

										
										

											141
											
                var errno syscall.Errno

										

										
										

											142
											
                if errors.As(opErr.Err, &errno) {

										

										
										

											143
											
                        switch errno {

										

										
										

											144
											
                        case syscall.ECONNREFUSED, syscall.ENETUNREACH, syscall.EHOSTUNREACH, syscall.ETIMEDOUT:

										

										
										

											145
											
                                return true

										

										
										

											146
											
                        }

										

										
										

											147
											
                }

										

										
										

											148
											
                // DNS resolution failures

										

										
										

											149
											
                var dnserr *net.DNSError

										

										
										

											150
											
                if errors.As(opErr.Err, &dnserr) {

										

										
										

											151
											
                        return true

										

										
										

											152
											
                }

										

										
										

											153
											
        }

										

										
										

											154
											
        // Direct DNS errors

										

										
										

											155
											
        var dnserr *net.DNSError

										

										
										

											156
											
        return errors.As(err, &dnserr)

										

										
										

											157
											
}

func Client.performAtomicHealthTest(...)
									
										
									
									

								

								
/home/sky/triggerX/backend/triggerx-backend/pkg/client/redis/health.go

								

									
										
										

											129
											
func (c *Client) performAtomicHealthTest(ctx context.Context, key, value string, ttl time.Duration) (bool, bool, bool, string) {

										

										
										

											130
											
        // Lua script that atomically sets a key, gets its value, and deletes it

										

										
										

											131
											
        // Returns: [set_result, get_result, delete_result]

										

										
										

											132
											
        // set_result: 1 if key was set, 0 if failed

										

										
										

											133
											
        // get_result: the value that was retrieved, or nil if failed

										

										
										

											134
											
        // delete_result: 1 if key was deleted, 0 if failed

										

										
										

											135
											
        script := `

										

										
										

											136
											
        local set_result = redis.call("set", KEYS[1], ARGV[1], "ex", ARGV[2])

										

										
										

											137
											
        if set_result == "OK" then

										

										
										

											138
											
                local get_result = redis.call("get", KEYS[1])

										

										
										

											139
											
                local delete_result = redis.call("del", KEYS[1])

										

										
										

											140
											
                return {1, get_result, delete_result}

										

										
										

											141
											
        else

										

										
										

											142
											
                return {0, nil, 0}

										

										
										

											143

func (l *Lock) Acquire(ctx context.Context) (bool, error) {

										

										
										

											67

											68

											71

											81

											84

											85

											91

func (l *Lock) Release(ctx context.Context) error {

										

										
										

											130
											
        // This Lua script atomically gets the key, compares its value to our token,

										

										
										

											131
											
        // and deletes it if they match. This prevents deleting a lock acquired by another client.

										

										
										

											132
											
        script := `

										

										
										

											133
											
        if redis.call("get", KEYS[1]) == ARGV[1] then

										

										
										

											134
											
                return redis.call("del", KEYS[1])

										

										
										

											135
											
        else

										

										
										

											136
											
                return 0

										

										
										

											137
											
        end`

										

										
										

											138
											

										

										
										

											139
											
        // We use Eval to run the script. It is wrapped in our client's retry logic for network errors.

										

										
										

											140
											
        res, err := l.client.Eval(ctx, script, []string{l.key}, l.token)

										

										
										

											141
											
        if err != nil {

										

										
										

											142
											
                return fmt.Errorf("failed to execute lock release script: %w", err)

										

										
										

											143
											
        }

										

										
										

											144
											

										

										
										

											145
											
        // The script returns 1 if the key was deleted, 0 otherwise.

										

										
										

											146
											
        if val, ok := res.(int64); !ok || val == 0 {

										

										
										

											147
											
                return ErrLockNotAcquired

										

										
										

											148
											
        }

										

										
										

											149
											

										

										
										

											150
											
        return nil

										

										
										

											151

func VerifySignature(message string, signature string, signerAddress string) (bool, error) {

										

										
										

											57

											59
											

										

										
										

											60

											61

											62

											64
											

										

										
										

											65

											68
											

										

										
										

											69

											71

											72
											

										

										
										

											73

											81

											83

func gocqlShouldRetry(...)
									
										
									
									

								

								
/home/sky/triggerX/backend/triggerx-backend/pkg/database/retry_codes.go

								

									
										
										

											12
											
func gocqlShouldRetry(err error) bool {

										

										
										

											13
											
        if err == nil {

										

										
										

											14
											
                return false

										

										
										

											15
											
        }

										

										
										

											16
											

										

										
										

											17
											
        // Do NOT retry if the resource is simply not found. This is a final state.

										

										
										

											18
											
        if errors.Is(err, gocql.ErrNotFound) {

										

										
										

											19
											
                return false

										

										
										

											20
											
        }

										

										
										

											21
											

										

										
										

											22
											
        // Do NOT retry on query validation errors (e.g., syntax error).

										

										
										

											23
											
        // Check for invalid query error codes (8704 = Invalid query, 2000 = Syntax error)

										

										
										

											24
											
        var reqErr gocql.RequestError

										

										
										

											25
											
        if errors.As(err, &reqErr) {

										

										
										

											26
											
                code := reqErr.Code()

										

										
										

											27
											
                // Error codes for invalid queries: 8704 (Invalid query), 2000 (Syntax error)

										

										
										

											28
											
                if code == 8704 || code == 2000 {

										

										
										

											29
											
                        return false

										

										
										

											30
											
                }

										

										
										

											31
											
        }

										

										
										

											32
											

										

										
										

											33
											
        // Use type assertions for specific, known-retryable gocql error types.

										

										
										

											34
											
        // This is the most reliable method.

										

										
										

											35
											
        switch err.(type) {

										

										
										

											36
											
        case *gocql.RequestErrWriteTimeout,

										

										
										

											37
											
                *gocql.RequestErrReadTimeout,

										

										
										

											38
											
                *gocql.RequestErrUnavailable,

										

										
										

											39
											
                *gocql.RequestErrReadFailure,

										

										
										

											40
											
                *gocql.RequestErrWriteFailure:

										

										
										

											41
											
                return true

										

										
										

											42
											
        }

										

										
										

											43
											

										

										
										

											44
											
        // Check for generic network errors, which are often retryable.

										

										
										

											45
											
        var netErr net.Error

										

										
										

											46
											
        if errors.As(err, &netErr) && netErr.Timeout() {

										

										
										

											47
											
                return true

										

										
										

											48
											
        }

										

										
										

											49
											

										

										
										

											50
											
        // As a fallback, check for common error strings. This is more brittle but can

										

										
										

											51
											
        // catch transient errors that don't conform to the types above.

										

										
										

											52
											
        errMsg := strings.ToLower(err.Error())

										

										
										

											53
											
        retryableMessages := []string{

										

										
										

											54
											
                "no connections available",

										

										
										

											55
											
                "connection reset by peer",

										

										
										

											56
											
                "i/o timeout",

										

										
										

											57
											
                "broken pipe",

										

										
										

											58
											
                "connection timed out",

										

										
										

											59
											
                "connection refused",

										

										
										

											60
											
        }

										

										
										

											61
											

										

										
										

											62
											
        for _, msg := range retryableMessages {

										

										
										

											63
											
                if strings.Contains(errMsg, msg) {

										

										
										

											64
											
                        return true

										

										
										

											65
											
                }

										

										
										

											66
											
        }

										

										
										

											67
											

										

										
										

											68
											
        return false

										

										
										

											69
											
}

func (p *ContainerPool) Close() error {

										

										
										

											756
											
        p.mutex.Lock()

										

										
										

											757
											
        defer p.mutex.Unlock()

										

										
										

											758
											

										

										
										

											759
											
        // Stop cleanup routine

										

										
										

											760
											
        if p.cleanupTicker != nil {

										

										
										

											761
											
                close(p.stopCleanup)

										

										
										

											762
											
        }

										

										
										

											763
											

										

										
										

											764
											
        // Cleanup all containers

										

										
										

											765
											
        for id := range p.containers {

										

										
										

											766
											
                if err := p.manager.CleanupContainer(context.Background(), id); err != nil {

										

										
										

											767
											
                        p.logger.Warnf("Failed to cleanup container %s: %v", id, err)

										

										
										

											768
											
                }

										

										
										

											769
											
        }

										

										
										

											770
											

										

										
										

											771
											
        p.containers = make(map[string]*types.PooledContainer)

										

										
										

											772

											773

											774

/home/sky/triggerX/backend/triggerx-backend/pkg/docker/container/pool.go

								

									
										
										

											637
											
func (p *ContainerPool) cleanup() {

										

										
										

											638
											
        p.mutex.Lock()

										

										
										

											639
											
        defer p.mutex.Unlock()

										

										
										

											640
											

										

										
										

											641
											
        now := time.Now()

										

										
										

											642
											
        containersToRemove := make([]string, 0)

										

										
										

											643
											

										

										
										

											644
											
        // Find containers that have been idle too long

										

										
										

											645
											
        for id, container := range p.containers {

										

										
										

											646
											
                if container.Status == types.ContainerStatusReady &&

										

										
										

											647
											
                        now.Sub(container.LastUsed) > p.config.IdleTimeout {

										

										
										

											648
											
                        containersToRemove = append(containersToRemove, id)

										

										
										

											649
											
                }

										

										
										

											650
											
        }

										

										
										

											651
											

										

										
										

											652
											
        // Remove idle containers (but keep minimum number)

										

										
										

											653
											
        readyCount := p.getReadyContainerCount()

										

										
										

											654
											
        for _, id := range containersToRemove {

										

										
										

											655
											
                if readyCount <= p.config.MinContainers {

										

										
										

											656
											
                        break

										

										
										

											657
											
                }

										

										
										

											658
											

										

										
										

											659
											
                if err := p.manager.CleanupContainer(context.Background(), id); err != nil {

										

										
										

											660
											
                        p.logger.Warnf("Failed to cleanup container %s: %v", id, err)

										

										
										

											661
											
                        continue

										

										
										

											662
											
                }

										

										
										

											663
											

										

										
										

											664
											
                delete(p.containers, id)

										

										
										

											665
											
                readyCount--

										

										
										

											666
											
                p.stats.DestroyedCount++

										

										
										

											667
											
        }

										

										
										

											668
											

										

										
										

											669
											
        if len(containersToRemove) > 0 {

										

										
										

											670
											
                p.logger.Infof("Cleaned up %d idle containers from %s language pool", len(containersToRemove), p.language)

										

										
										

											671
											
        }

										

										
										

											672
											

										

										
										

											673
											
        p.stats.LastCleanup = now

										

										
										

											674
											
        p.updateStats()

										

										
										

											675
											
}

func (p *ContainerPool) ReturnContainer(container *types.PooledContainer) error {

										

										
										

											171

											172
											

										

										
										

											173

											174

											175
											

										

										
										

											176

											178
											

										

										
										

											179

											180

											181

											182

											183
											
                        pooledContainer.Status = types.ContainerStatusError

                        pooledContainer.Error = err

										

										
										

											185
											
                        pooledContainer.IsReady = false

										

										
										

											186
											
                        p.updateStats()

										

										
										

											187
											

										

										
										

											188
											
                        // Try to cleanup the failed container

										

										
										

											189
											
                        if cleanupErr := p.manager.CleanupContainer(context.Background(), container.ID); cleanupErr != nil {

										

										
										

											190
											
                                p.logger.Warnf("Failed to cleanup failed container %s: %v", container.ID, cleanupErr)

										

										
										

											191
											
                        } else {

                                delete(p.containers, container.ID)

										

										
										

											193
											
                        }

										

										
										

											194
											

										

										
										

											195
											
                        return err

										

										
										

											196
											
                }

										

										
										

											197
											

										

										
										

											198
											
                p.logger.Debugf("Container %s reset successfully, marking as ready", container.ID)

										

										
										

											199
											
                pooledContainer.Status = types.ContainerStatusReady

										

										
										

											200
											
                pooledContainer.IsReady = true

										

										
										

											201
											
                pooledContainer.Error = nil // Clear any previous errors

										

										
										

											202
											
                p.updateStats()

										

										
										

											203
											

										

										
										

											204
											
                // Signal that a container is available

										

										
										

											205
											
                select {

										

										
										

											206
											
                case p.waitQueue <- struct{}{}:

										

										
										

											207
											
                default:

										

										
										

											208
											
                        // Channel is full, no one is waiting

										

										
										

											209
											
                }

										

										
										

											210
											

										

										
										

											211
											
                p.logger.Debugf("Returned container %s to %s language pool", container.ID, p.language)

										

										
										

											212
											
        } else {

										

										
										

											213
											
                p.logger.Warnf("Container %s not found in %s language pool", container.ID, p.language)

										

										
										

											214
											
        }

										

										
										

											215
											

										

										
										

											216
											
        return nil

										

										
										

											217
											
}

										

										
									
								

							

						

					
						

							

								

									
func ContainerPool.GetContainer(...)
									
										
									
									

								

								
/home/sky/triggerX/backend/triggerx-backend/pkg/docker/container/pool.go

								

									
										
										

											110
											
func (p *ContainerPool) GetContainer(ctx context.Context) (*types.PooledContainer, error) {

										

										
										

											111
											
        // Try to get a ready container

										

										
										

											112
											
        p.mutex.Lock()

										

										
										

											113
											
        for _, container := range p.containers {

										

										
										

											114
											
                // p.logger.Debugf("Checking container %s: status=%s, ready=%v", container.ID, container.Status, container.IsReady)

										

										
										

											115
											

										

										
										

											116
											
                if container.Status == types.ContainerStatusReady && container.IsReady {

										

										
										

											117
											
                        // p.logger.Debugf("Found ready container %s, verifying it's running", container.ID)

										

										
										

											118
											

										

										
										

											119
											
                        // Verify container is actually running before returning it

										

										
										

											120
											
                        inspect, err := p.manager.dockerClient.ContainerInspect(ctx, container.ID)

										

										
										

											121
											
                        if err != nil {

										

										
										

											122
											
                                p.logger.Warnf("Container %s health check failed during get: %v", container.ID, err)

										

										
										

											123
											
                                container.Status = types.ContainerStatusError

										

										
										

											124
											
                                container.Error = err

										

										
										

											125
											
                                continue

										

										
										

											126
											
                        }

										

										
										

											127
											

										

										
										

											128
											
                        // p.logger.Debugf("Container %s inspect result: status=%s, running=%v", container.ID, inspect.State.Status, inspect.State.Running)

										

										
										

											129
											

										

										
										

											130
											
                        if !inspect.State.Running {

										

										
										

											131
											
                                p.logger.Warnf("Container %s is not running, marking as error", container.ID)

										

										
										

											132
											
                                container.Status = types.ContainerStatusError

										

										
										

											133
											
                                container.IsReady = false

										

										
										

											134
											
                                continue

										

										
										

											135
											
                        }

										

										
										

											136
											

										

										
										

											137
											
                        p.logger.Debugf("Container %s verified as running, returning it", container.ID)

										

										
										

											138
											
                        container.Status = types.ContainerStatusRunning

										

										
										

											139
											
                        container.LastUsed = time.Now()

										

										
										

											140
											
                        p.updateStats()

										

										
										

											141
											
                        p.mutex.Unlock()

										

										
										

											142
											
                        return container, nil

										

										
										

											143
											
                }

										

										
										

											144
											
        }

										

										
										

											145
											
        p.mutex.Unlock()

										

										
										

											146
											

										

										
										

											147
											
        // No ready containers available, try to create a new one

										

										
										

											148
											
        if p.getTotalContainerCount() < p.config.MaxContainers {

										

										
										

											149
											
                container, err := p.createPreparedContainer(ctx)

										

										
										

											150
											
                if err != nil {

										

										
										

											151
											
                        return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to create container for language %s: %w", p.language, err)

										

										
										

											152
											
                }

										

										
										

											153
											
                container.Status = types.ContainerStatusRunning

										

										
										

											154
											
                container.LastUsed = time.Now()

										

										
										

											155
											
                return container, nil

										

										
										

											156
											
        }

										

										
										

											157
											

										

										
										

											158
											
        // Wait for a container to become available

										

										
										

											159
											
        select {

										

										
										

											160
											
        case <-p.waitQueue:

										

										
										

											161
											
                // Try again after waiting

										

										
										

											162
											
                return p.GetContainer(ctx)

										

										
										

											163
											
        case <-ctx.Done():

										

										
										

											164
											
                return nil, fmt.Errorf("timeout waiting for container: %w", ctx.Err())

										

										
										

											165
											
        case <-time.After(p.config.MaxWaitTime):

										

										
										

											166
											
                return nil, fmt.Errorf("timeout waiting for container in language pool %s", p.language)

										

										
										

											167
											
        }

										

										
										

											168
											
}

										

										
									
								

							

						

					
						

							

								

									
func Manager.executeCode(...)
									
										
									
									

								

								
/home/sky/triggerX/backend/triggerx-backend/pkg/docker/container/manager.go

								

									
										
										

											625
											
func (m *Manager) executeCode(ctx context.Context, containerID string, language types.Language) (*types.ExecutionResult, error) {

										

										
										

											626
											
        result := &types.ExecutionResult{}

										

										
										

											627
											
        var executionStartTime time.Time

										

										
										

											628
											
        var executionEndTime time.Time

										

										
										

											629
											
        var codeExecutionTime time.Duration

										

										
										

											630
											
        executionStarted := false

										

										
										

											631
											
        var outputBuffer bytes.Buffer

										

										
										

											632
											

										

										
										

											633
											
        // Get language-specific setup script

										

										
										

											634
											
        langConfig, exists := m.config.GetLanguagePoolConfig(language)

										

										
										

											635
											
        if !exists {

										

										
										

											636
											
                return nil, fmt.Errorf("no configuration found for language: %s", language)

										

										
										

											637
											
        }

										

										
										

											638
											
        execCmd := []string{"sh", "-c", langConfig.Config.SetupScript}

										

										
										

											639
											

										

										
										

											640
											
        execConfig := container.ExecOptions{

										

										
										

											641
											
                Cmd:          execCmd,

										

										
										

											642
											
                AttachStdout: true,

										

										
										

											643
											
                AttachStderr: true,

										

										
										

											644
											
        }

										

										
										

											645
											

										

										
										

											646
											
        execResp, err := m.dockerClient.ContainerExecCreate(ctx, containerID, execConfig)

										

										
										

											647
											
        if err != nil {

										

										
										

											648
											
                return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to create exec: %w", err)

										

										
										

											649
											
        }

										

										
										

											650
											

										

										
										

											651
											
        execAttachResp, err := m.dockerClient.ContainerExecAttach(ctx, execResp.ID, container.ExecAttachOptions{

										

										
										

											652
											
                Detach: false,

										

										
										

											653
											
                Tty:    true,

										

										
										

											654
											
        })

										

										
										

											655
											
        if err != nil {

										

										
										

											656
											
                return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to attach to exec: %w", err)

										

										
										

											657
											
        }

										

										
										

											658
											
        defer execAttachResp.Close()

										

										
										

											659
											
        scanner := bufio.NewScanner(execAttachResp.Reader)

										

										
										

											660
											

										

										
										

											661
											
        // Execute the command

										

										
										

											662
											
        err = m.dockerClient.ContainerExecStart(ctx, execResp.ID, container.ExecStartOptions{})

										

										
										

											663
											
        if err != nil {

										

										
										

											664
											
                return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to start exec: %w", err)

										

										
										

											665
											
        }

										

										
										

											666
											

										

										
										

											667
											
        for scanner.Scan() {

										

										
										

											668
											
                line := scanner.Text()

										

										
										

											669
											
                // m.logger.Debugf("Container Log: %s\n", line)

										

										
										

											670
											

										

										
										

											671
											
                if strings.Contains(line, "START_EXECUTION") {

										

										
										

											672
											
                        executionStartTime = time.Now().UTC()

										

										
										

											673
											
                        executionStarted = true

										

										
										

											674
											
                } else if strings.Contains(line, "END_EXECUTION") && executionStarted {

										

										
										

											675
											
                        executionEndTime = time.Now().UTC()

										

										
										

											676
											
                        codeExecutionTime = executionEndTime.Sub(executionStartTime)

										

										
										

											677
											
                        // m.logger.Debugf("Code execution completed in: %v\n", codeExecutionTime)

										

										
										

											678
											
                        break

										

										
										

											679
											
                } else if executionStarted {

										

										
										

											680
											
                        outputBuffer.WriteString(line)

										

										
										

											681
											
                        // m.logger.Debugf("Container Log: %s\n", line)

										

										
										

											682
											
                }

										

										
										

											683
											
        }

										

										
										

											684
											

										

										
										

											685
											
        // Wait for exec to finish (in case END_EXECUTION is not printed)

										

										
										

											686
											
        for {

										

										
										

											687
											
                inspectResp, err := m.dockerClient.ContainerExecInspect(ctx, execResp.ID)

										

										
										

											688
											
                if err != nil {

										

										
										

											689
											
                        return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to inspect exec: %w", err)

										

										
										

											690
											
                }

										

										
										

											691
											
                if !inspectResp.Running {

										

										
										

											692
											
                        if !executionStarted || codeExecutionTime == 0 {

										

										
										

											693
											
                                codeExecutionTime = time.Since(executionStartTime)

										

										
										

											694
											
                                m.logger.Debugf("Warning: Could not determine precise code execution time, using container execution time instead")

										

										
										

											695
											
                        }

										

										
										

											696
											
                        result.Success = inspectResp.ExitCode == 0

										

										
										

											697
											
                        if inspectResp.ExitCode != 0 {

										

										
										

											698
											
                                result.Error = fmt.Errorf("execution failed with exit code: %d", inspectResp.ExitCode)

										

										
										

											699
											
                        }

										

										
										

											700
											
                        break

										

										
										

											701
											
                }

										

										
										

											702
											
                time.Sleep(100 * time.Millisecond)

										

										
										

											703
											
        }

										

										
										

											704
											

										

										
										

											705
											
        result.Output = outputBuffer.String()

										

										
										

											706
											
        result.Stats.ExecutionTime = codeExecutionTime

										

										
										

											707
											
        return result, nil

										

										
										

											708
											
}

func ContainerLifecycle.GetContainerStats(...)
									
										
									
									

								

								
/home/sky/triggerX/backend/triggerx-backend/pkg/docker/container/lifecycle.go

								

									
										
										

											158
											
func (cl *ContainerLifecycle) GetContainerStats(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*types.DockerResourceStats, error) {

										

										
										

											159
											
        stats, err := cl.manager.dockerClient.ContainerStats(ctx, containerID, false)

										

										
										

											160
											
        if err != nil {

										

										
										

											161
											
                return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to get container stats: %w", err)

										

										
										

											162
											
        }

										

										
										

											163
											
        defer func() {

										

										
										

											164
											
                err := stats.Body.Close()

										

										
										

											165
											
                if err != nil {

										

										
										

											166
											
                        cl.logger.Errorf("Failed to close container stats body: %v", err)

										

										
										

											167
											
                }

										

										
										

											168
											
        }()

										

										
										

											169
											

										

										
										

											170
											
        // Docker stats stream JSON objects; decode the first one

										

										
										

											171
											
        var dockerStats container.StatsResponse

										

										
										

											172
											
        dec := json.NewDecoder(stats.Body)

										

										
										

											173
											
        if err := dec.Decode(&dockerStats); err != nil && err != io.EOF {

										

										
										

											174
											
                return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to decode container stats: %w", err)

										

										
										

											175
											
        }

										

										
										

											176
											

										

										
										

											177
											
        // Calculate CPU usage percent (see Docker's formula)

										

										
										

											178
											
        var cpuPercent float64

										

										
										

											179
											
        cpuDelta := float64(dockerStats.CPUStats.CPUUsage.TotalUsage - dockerStats.PreCPUStats.CPUUsage.TotalUsage)

										

										
										

											180
											
        systemDelta := float64(dockerStats.CPUStats.SystemUsage - dockerStats.PreCPUStats.SystemUsage)

										

										
										

											181
											
        if systemDelta > 0.0 && cpuDelta > 0.0 {

										

										
										

											182
											
                cpuPercent = (cpuDelta / systemDelta) * float64(len(dockerStats.CPUStats.CPUUsage.PercpuUsage)) * 100.0

										

										
										

											183
											
        }

										

										
										

											184
											

										

										
										

											185
											
        // Network stats (sum all interfaces)

										

										
										

											186
											
        var rxBytes, txBytes uint64

										

										
										

											187
											
        if dockerStats.Networks != nil {

										

										
										

											188
											
                for _, v := range dockerStats.Networks {

										

										
										

											189
											
                        rxBytes += v.RxBytes

										

										
										

											190
											
                        txBytes += v.TxBytes

										

										
										

											191
											
                }

										

										
										

											192
											
        }

										

										
										

											193
											

										

										
										

											194
											
        resourceStats := &types.DockerResourceStats{

										

										
										

											195
											
                MemoryUsage:   dockerStats.MemoryStats.Usage,

										

										
										

											196
											
                CPUPercentage: cpuPercent,

										

										
										

											197
											
                NetworkRx:     rxBytes,

										

										
										

											198
											
                NetworkTx:     txBytes,

										

										
										

											199
											
                BlockRead:     sumBlkioServiceBytes(dockerStats.BlkioStats.IoServiceBytesRecursive, "Read"),

										

										
										

											200
											
                BlockWrite:    sumBlkioServiceBytes(dockerStats.BlkioStats.IoServiceBytesRecursive, "Write"),

										

										
										

											201
											
                RxBytes:       rxBytes,

										

										
										

											202
											
                TxBytes:       txBytes,

										

										
										

											203
											
                ExecutionTime: time.Duration(dockerStats.Read.UnixNano()), // This is the stats timestamp; adjust as needed

										

										
										

											204
											
        }

										

										
										

											205
											

										

										
										

											206
											
        return resourceStats, nil

										

										
										

											207
											
}

func (cl *ContainerLifecycle) HealthCheck(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error {

											411

func (p *ContainerPool) createContainer(ctx context.Context, codePath string) (string, error) {

											485

        for _, lang := range languages {

										

										
										

											92

											106

											107
											

										

										
										

											108

											285

											289

func (ep *ExecutionPipeline) calculateFees(execCtx *types.ExecutionContext) float64 {

										

										
										

											174
											
        // Basic fee calculation

										

										
										

											175

											178
											

										

										
										

											179
											
        // Add complexity factor if available

										

										
										

											180
											
        complexityFee := 0.0

										

										
										

											181
											
        if _, ok := execCtx.Metadata["complexity"]; ok {

										

										
										

											182
											
                // Parse complexity and apply factor

										

										
										

											183
											
                // This is a simplified calculation

											185
											
        }

										

										
										

											186
											

										

										
										

											187
											
        return baseFee + timeFee + complexityFee

											206
											
func (em *ExecutionMonitor) GetAlerts(severity string, limit int) []Alert {

										

										
										

											207
											
        em.mutex.RLock()

										

										
										

											208
											
        defer em.mutex.RUnlock()

										

										
										

											209
											

										

										
										

											210
											
        filteredAlerts := make([]Alert, 0)

										

										
										

											211
											

										

										
										

											212
											
        for _, alert := range em.alerts {

										

										
										

											213
											
                if severity == "" || alert.Severity == severity {

										

										
										

											214
											
                        filteredAlerts = append(filteredAlerts, alert)

										

										
										

											215
											
                }

										

										
										

											216
											
        }

										

										
										

											217
											

										

										
										

											218
											
        // Sort by timestamp (newest first)

										

										
										

											219
											
        for i := 0; i < len(filteredAlerts)-1; i++ {

										

										
										

											220
											
                for j := i + 1; j < len(filteredAlerts); j++ {

										

										
										

											221
											
                        if filteredAlerts[i].Timestamp.Before(filteredAlerts[j].Timestamp) {

										

										
										

											222
											
                                filteredAlerts[i], filteredAlerts[j] = filteredAlerts[j], filteredAlerts[i]

										

										
										

											223
											
                        }

										

										
										

											224
											
                }

										

										
										

											225
											
        }

										

										
										

											226
											

										

										
										

											227
											
        // Apply limit

										

										
										

											228
											
        if limit > 0 && len(filteredAlerts) > limit {

										

										
										

											229
											
                filteredAlerts = filteredAlerts[:limit]

										

										
										

											230
											
        }

										

										
										

											231
											

										

										
										

											232
											
        return filteredAlerts

										

										
										

											233
											
}

											83
											
func (em *ExecutionMonitor) performHealthCheck() {

										

										
										

											84
											
        em.logger.Debugf("Performing health check")

										

										
										

											85
											

										

										
										

											86
											
        // Check active executions

										

										
										

											87
											
        activeExecutions := em.pipeline.GetActiveExecutions()

										

										
										

											88
											

										

										
										

											89
											
        // Check for stuck executions (default max time: 5 minutes)

										

										
										

											90
											
        maxExecutionTime := 5 * time.Minute

										

										
										

											91
											
        for _, exec := range activeExecutions {

										

										
										

											92
											
                duration := time.Since(exec.StartedAt)

										

										
										

											93
											
                if duration > maxExecutionTime {

										

										
										

											94
											
                        em.createAlert("execution_timeout", fmt.Sprintf("Execution %s has exceeded max time: %v", exec.TraceID, duration), "warning")

										

										
										

											95
											
                }

										

										
										

											96
											
        }

										

										
										

											97
											

										

										
										

											98
											
        // Check pipeline statistics

func (ep *ExecutionPipeline) Execute(ctx context.Context, fileURL string, noOfAttesters int) (*types.ExecutionResult, error) {

										

										
										

											48
											
        startTime := time.Now()

										

										
										

											49
											
        executionID := generateExecutionID()

										

										
										

											50
											

										

										
										

											51

											52
											

										

										
										

											53
											
        // Create execution context

										

										
										

											54
											
        execCtx := &types.ExecutionContext{

										

										
										

											55
											
                FileURL:       fileURL,

										

										
										

											56
											
                NoOfAttesters: noOfAttesters,

										

										
										

											57
											
                TraceID:       executionID,

										

										
										

											58
											
                StartedAt:     startTime,

										

										
										

											59
											
                Metadata:      make(map[string]string),

										

										
										

											60
											
        }

										

										
										

											61
											

										

										
										

											62
											
        // Track execution

										

										
										

											63
											
        ep.mutex.Lock()

										

										
										

											64

											65
											
        ep.mutex.Unlock()

										

										
										

											66
											

										

										
										

											67
											
        defer func() {

										

										
										

											68
											
                // Remove from active executions

										

										
										

											69
											
                ep.mutex.Lock()

										

										
										

											70

											71
											
                ep.mutex.Unlock()

										

										
										

											72
											

										

										
										

											73
											
                // Update statistics

										

										
										

											74
											
                duration := time.Since(startTime)

										

										
										

											75
											
                ep.updateStats(true, duration, 0.0)

										

										
										

											76

											77
											

										

										
										

											78
											
        // Execute pipeline stages

										

										
										

											79

											80
											
        if err != nil {

										

										
										

											81
											
                execCtx.CompletedAt = time.Now()

										

										
										

											82
											
                ep.updateStats(false, time.Since(startTime), 0.0)

										

										
										

											83

											84

											85

											88
											

										

										
										

											89

func (em *ExecutionMonitor) GetHealthStatus() *HealthStatus {

										

										
										

											149

											150
											
        defer em.mutex.RUnlock()

										

										
										

											151
											

										

										
										

											152
											
        // Calculate overall health score

										

										
										

											153
											
        healthScore := 100.0

										

										
										

											154
											

										

										
										

											155
											
        // Reduce score based on alerts

										

										
										

											156
											
        criticalAlerts := 0

										

										
										

											157
											
        warningAlerts := 0

										

										
										

											158
											

										

										
										

											159

											160

											161

											162

											163

											164

											165

											166

											168
											
        }

										

										
										

											169
											

										

										
										

											170

											172

                status = "critical"

											182

											183
											

										

										
										

											184
											
        return &HealthStatus{

func (ep *ExecutionPipeline) updateStats(success bool, duration time.Duration, complexity float64) {

										

										
										

											241
											
        ep.mutex.Lock()

										

										
										

											242
											
        defer ep.mutex.Unlock()

										

										
										

											243
											

										

										
										

											244
											
        ep.stats.TotalExecutions++

										

										
										

											245
											
        ep.stats.LastExecution = time.Now()

										

										
										

											246
											

										

										
										

											247
											
        if success {

										

										
										

											248
											
                ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions++

										

										
										

											249
											
        } else {

										

										
										

											250
											
                ep.stats.FailedExecutions++

										

										
										

											251
											
        }

										

										
										

											252
											

										

										
										

											253
											
        // Update execution time statistics

										

										
										

											254
											
        if ep.stats.MinExecutionTime == 0 || duration < ep.stats.MinExecutionTime {

										

										
										

											255
											
                ep.stats.MinExecutionTime = duration

										

										
										

											256
											
        }

										

										
										

											257
											
        if duration > ep.stats.MaxExecutionTime {

										

										
										

											258
											
                ep.stats.MaxExecutionTime = duration

										

										
										

											259
											
        }

										

										
										

											260
											

										

										
										

											261
											
        // Calculate average execution time - only if we have successful executions

										

										
										

											262
											
        if ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions > 0 {

										

										
										

											263
											
                if ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions == 1 {

										

										
										

											264
											
                        // First successful execution

										

										
										

											265
											
                        ep.stats.AverageExecutionTime = duration

										

										
										

											266
											
                } else {

										

										
										

											267
											
                        // Calculate running average

										

										
										

											268
											
                        totalDuration := ep.stats.AverageExecutionTime * time.Duration(ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions-1)

										

										
										

											269
											
                        totalDuration += duration

										

										
										

											270
											
                        ep.stats.AverageExecutionTime = totalDuration / time.Duration(ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions)

										

										
										

											271
											
                }

										

										
										

											272
											
        }

										

										
										

											273
											

										

										
										

											274
											
        // Update cost statistics

										

										
										

											275
											
        cost := ep.calculateCost(duration, complexity)

										

										
										

											276
											
        ep.stats.TotalCost += cost

										

										
										

											277
											

										

										
										

											278
											
        // Calculate average cost - only if we have successful executions

										

										
										

											279
											
        if ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions > 0 {

										

										
										

											280
											
                ep.stats.AverageCost = ep.stats.TotalCost / float64(ep.stats.SuccessfulExecutions)

										

										
										

											281
											
        }

										

										
										

											282
											
}

func fileCache.ensureSpace(...)
									
										
									
									

								

								
/home/sky/triggerX/backend/triggerx-backend/pkg/docker/file/cache.go

								

									
										
										

											185
											
func (c *fileCache) ensureSpace(requiredSize int64) error {

										

										
										

											186
											
        c.mutex.Lock()

										

										
										

											187
											
        defer c.mutex.Unlock()

										

										
										

											188
											

										

										
										

											189
											
        // If we have enough space, no need to evict

										

										
										

											190
											
        if c.stats.Size+requiredSize <= c.config.MaxCacheSize {

										

										
										

											191
											
                return nil

										

										
										

											192
											
        }

										

										
										

											193
											

										

										
										

											194
											
        // Need to evict files

										

										
										

											195
											
        evictionSize := c.stats.Size + requiredSize - c.config.MaxCacheSize

										

										
										

											196
											

										

										
										

											197
											
        // Sort files by last accessed time (oldest first)

										

										
										

											198
											
        type fileEntry struct {

										

										
										

											199
											
                hash string

										

										
										

											200
											
                file *cachedFile

										

										
										

											201
											
        }

										

										
										

											202
											

										

										
										

											203
											
        var files []fileEntry

										

										
										

											204
											
        for hash, file := range c.fileCache {

										

										
										

											205
											
                files = append(files, fileEntry{hash: hash, file: file})

										

										
										

											206
											
        }

										

										
										

											207
											

										

										
										

											208
											
        // Sort by last accessed time (oldest first)

										

										
										

											209
											
        for i := 0; i < len(files)-1; i++ {

										

										
										

											210
											
                for j := i + 1; j < len(files); j++ {

										

										
										

											211
											
                        if files[i].file.LastAccessed.After(files[j].file.LastAccessed) {

										

										
										

											212
											
                                files[i], files[j] = files[j], files[i]

										

										
										

											213
											
                        }

										

										
										

											214
											
                }

										

										
										

											215
											
        }

										

										
										

											216
											

										

										
										

											217
											
        // Evict files until we have enough space

										

										
										

											218
											
        evictedSize := int64(0)

										

										
										

											219
											
        for _, entry := range files {

										

										
										

											220
											
                if evictedSize >= evictionSize {

										

										
										

											221
											
                        break

										

										
										

											222
											
                }

										

										
										

											223
											

										

										
										

											224
											
                // Remove file from disk

										

										
										

											225
											
                if err := c.fs.Remove(entry.file.Path); err != nil {

										

										
										

											226
											
                        c.logger.Warnf("Failed to remove cached file: %v", err)

										

										
										

											227
											
                        continue

										

										
										

											228
											
                }

										

										
										

											229
											

										

										
										

											230
											
                // Remove from cache

										

										
										

											231
											
                delete(c.fileCache, entry.hash)

										

										
										

											232
											
                evictedSize += entry.file.Size

										

										
										

											233
											
                c.stats.EvictionCount++

										

										
										

											234
											
                c.stats.ItemCount--

										

										
										

											235
											
                c.stats.Size -= entry.file.Size

										

										
										

											236
											

										

										
										

											237
											
                c.logger.Debugf("Evicted cached file: %s (size: %d bytes)", entry.hash, entry.file.Size)

										

										
										

											238
											
        }

										

										
										

											239
											

										

										
										

											240
											
        c.logger.Infof("Evicted %d bytes (%d files) from cache", evictedSize, c.stats.EvictionCount)

										

										
										

											241
											

										

										
										

											242
											
        // Save updated metadata after eviction

										

										
										

											243
											
        if err := c.saveMetadata(); err != nil {

										

										
										

											244
											
                c.logger.Warnf("Failed to save cache metadata after eviction: %v", err)

										

										
										

											245
											
        }

										

										
										

											246
											

										

										
										

											247
											
        return nil

										

										
										

											248
											
}

											109
											
func (c *fileCache) accessCachedFile(cachedFile *cachedFile) (string, error) {

										

										
										

											110
											
        // Check if file still exists on disk

										

										
										

											111
											
        if _, err := c.fs.Stat(cachedFile.Path); os.IsNotExist(err) {

										

										
										

											112
											
                // File was deleted, remove from cache

										

										
										

											113
											
                c.mutex.Lock()

										

										
										

											114
											
                delete(c.fileCache, cachedFile.Hash)

										

										
										

											115
											
                c.stats.ItemCount--

										

										
										

											116
											
                c.stats.Size -= cachedFile.Size

										

										
										

											117
											
                c.mutex.Unlock()

										

										
										

											118
											

										

										
										

											119
											
                // Save updated metadata

										

										
										

											120
											
                if saveErr := c.saveMetadata(); saveErr != nil {

										

										
										

											121
											
                        c.logger.Warnf("Failed to save cache metadata after removal: %v", saveErr)

										

										
										

											122
											
                }

										

										
										

											123
											

										

										
										

											124
											
                return "", fmt.Errorf("cached file not found on disk: %s", cachedFile.Path)

										

										
										

											125
											
        }

										

										
										

											126
											

										

										
										

											127
											
        // Update hit count and hit rate

										

										
										

											128
											
        c.statsMutex.Lock()

										

										
										

											129
											
        c.stats.HitCount++

										

										
										

											130
											
        c.updateHitRate()

										

										
										

											131
											
        c.statsMutex.Unlock()

										

										
										

											132
											

										

										
										

											133
											
        cachedFile.LastAccessed = time.Now()

										

										
										

											134
											

										

										
										

											135
											
        // Save metadata to persist access time

										

										
										

											136
											
        if err := c.saveMetadata(); err != nil {

										

										
										

											137
											
                c.logger.Warnf("Failed to save cache metadata after access: %v", err)

										

										
										

											138
											
        }

										

										
										

											139
											

										

										
										

											140
											
        return cachedFile.Path, nil

										

										
										

											141
											
}

func (r *SequentialRotator) cleanupOldFiles() {

										

										
										

											162

											169

											183

											184

                baseName := filepath.Base(file)

											187

											188

											189
											
                        if s, err := strconv.Atoi(parts[len(parts)-2]); err == nil {

										

										
										

											190
											
                                seq = s

										

										
										

											191
											
                        }

										

										
										

											192

											193
											

										

										
										

											194

											205

											210

											212

											216

                // Fallback to a less random source if crypto/rand fails

										

										
										

											65
											
                return math.Mod(float64(time.Now().UnixNano()), 1000) / 1000.0

										

										
										

											66
											
        }

										

										
										

											67
											
        return float64(binary.BigEndian.Uint64(b[:])) / (1 << 64)

										

										
										

											68
											
}

											192
											
func (ai *AuthInterceptor) OptionalAuth() grpc.UnaryServerInterceptor {

										

										
										

											193
											
        return func(ctx context.Context, req interface{}, info *grpc.UnaryServerInfo, handler grpc.UnaryHandler) (interface{}, error) {

										

										
										

											194
											
                // Try to authenticate, but don't fail if no token is provided

										

										
										

											195
											
                claims, err := ai.AuthenticateRequest(ctx)

										

										
										

											196
											
                if err == nil {

										

										
										

											197
											
                        // Authentication successful, add claims to context

										

										
										

											198
											
                        ctx = ai.addClaimsToContext(ctx, claims)

										

										
										

											199
											
                }

										

										
										

											200
											
                // If authentication fails, continue without claims

										

										
										

											201
											

										

										
										

											202
											
                return handler(ctx, req)

										

										
										

											203
											
        }

										

										
										

											204
											
}

func (am *AuthMiddleware) ExtractTokenFromMetadata(ctx context.Context) (string, error) {

										

										
										

											100

											101
											
        if !ok {

										

										
										

											102
											
                return "", fmt.Errorf("no metadata found")

										

										
										

											103

											104
											

										

										
										

											105
											
        // Try to get token from Authorization header

										

										
										

											106
											
        authHeaders := md.Get("authorization")

										

										
										

											107
											
        if len(authHeaders) > 0 {

										

										
										

											108
											
                token := authHeaders[0]

										

										
										

											109
											
                if token != "" {

										

										
										

											110
											
                        return token, nil

										

										
										

											111
											
                }

										

										
										

											112
											
        }

										

										
										

											113
											

										

										
										

											114
											
        // Try to get token from x-auth-token header

										

										
										

											115
											
        authTokens := md.Get("x-auth-token")

										

										
										

											116
											
        if len(authTokens) > 0 {

										

										
										

											117
											
                token := authTokens[0]

										

										
										

											118
											
                if token != "" {

										

										
										

											119
											
                        return token, nil

										

										
										

											120
											
                }

										

										
										

											121
											
        }

										

										
										

											122
											

										

										
										

											123
											
        // Try to get token from x-jwt-token header

										

										
										

											124
											
        jwtTokens := md.Get("x-jwt-token")

										

										
										

											125
											
        if len(jwtTokens) > 0 {

										

										
										

											126
											
                token := jwtTokens[0]

										

										
										

											127
											
                if token != "" {

										

										
										

											128
											
                        return token, nil

										

										
										

											129
											
                }

										

										
										

											130
											
        }

										

										
										

											131
											

										

										
										

											132
											
        return "", fmt.Errorf("no authentication token found in metadata")

										

										
										

											133
											
}

func isRetryableError(err error, retryableCodes []codes.Code) bool {

										

										
										

											67
											
        if err == nil {

										

										
										

											68
											
                return false

										

										
										

											69
											
        }

										

										
										

											70
											

										

										
										

											71
											
        // Check if it's a gRPC status error

										

										
										

											72
											
        if st, ok := status.FromError(err); ok {

										

										
										

											73
											
                for _, code := range retryableCodes {

										

										
										

											74
											
                        if st.Code() == code {

										

										
										

											75
											
                                return true

										

										
										

											76
											
                        }

										

										
										

											77
											
                }

										

										
										

											78
											
        }

										

										
										

											79
											

										

										
										

											80
											
        // Check for connection errors

										

										
										

											81
											
        if st, ok := status.FromError(err); ok && st.Code() == codes.Canceled {

										

										
										

											82
											
                return true

										

										
										

											83
											
        }

										

										
										

											84
											

										

										
										

											85
											
        return false

										

										
										

											86
											
}

											80

											101

											102
											
        default:

											108
