                } else {

										

										
										

											92
											
                        // Use direct connection if no registry

										

										
										

											93
											
                        serviceInfo = &rpcpkg.ServiceInfo{

										

										
										

											94
											
                                Address: c.config.ServiceName, // Assume it's a direct address

										

										
										

											95
											
                        }

											97

											100
											
                if err != nil {

											38
											
func (p *ConnectionPool) GetConnection(ctx context.Context, address string) (*grpc.ClientConn, error) {

										

										
										

											39
											
        p.mu.Lock()

										

										
										

											40
											
        defer p.mu.Unlock()

										

										
										

											41
											

										

										
										

											42
											
        if p.closed {

										

										
										

											43
											
                return nil, fmt.Errorf("connection pool is closed")

										

										
										

											44
											
        }

										

										
										

											45
											

										

										
										

											46
											
        // Update address if needed

										

										
										

											47
											
        if p.address == "" {

										

										
										

											48
											
                p.address = address

										

										
										

											49
											
        }

										

										
										

											50
											

										

										
										

											51
											
        // Try to get existing connection

										

										
										

											52
											
        select {

										

										
										

											53
											
        case conn := <-p.connections:

										

										
										

											54
											
                // Test connection health

										

										
										

											55
											
                if p.isConnectionHealthy(conn) {

										

										
										

											56
											
                        return conn, nil

										

										
										

											57
											
                }

										

										
										

											58
											
                // Connection is unhealthy, close it and create new one

										

										
										

											59
											
                if err := conn.Close(); err != nil {

										

										
										

											60
											
                        p.logger.Errorf("Failed to close connection: %v", err)

										

										
										

											61
											
                }

										

										
										

											62
											
        default:

										

										
										

											63
											
                // No connection available, create new one if under limit

										

										
										

											64
											
                if len(p.connections) < p.maxSize {

										

										
										

											65
											
                        return p.createConnection(address)

										

										
										

											66
											
                }

										

										
										

											67
											
        }

										

										
										

											68
											

										

										
										

											69
											
        // Wait for available connection

										

										
										

											70
											
        select {

										

										
										

											71
											
        case conn := <-p.connections:

										

										
										

											72
											
                return conn, nil

										

										
										

											73
											
        case <-ctx.Done():

										

										
										

											74
											
                return nil, fmt.Errorf("timeout waiting for connection: %w", ctx.Err())

										

										
										

											75
											
        }

										

										
										

											76
											
}

func (c *Client) makeGRPCCall(ctx context.Context, conn *grpc.ClientConn, method string, request interface{}, response interface{}) error {

										

										
										

											132
											
        // Create call context with timeout

										

										
										

											133
											
        callCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, c.config.Timeout)

										

										
										

											134
											
        defer cancel()

										

										
										

											135
											

										

										
										

											136
											
        // Create gRPC client

										

										
										

											137
											
        client := rpcproto.NewGenericServiceClient(conn)

										

										
										

											138
											

										

										
										

											139
											
        // Convert request to Any

										

										
										

											140
											
        var payload *anypb.Any

										

										
										

											141
											
        if request != nil {

										

										
										

											142
											
                if protoMsg, ok := request.(proto.Message); ok {

										

										
										

											143
											
                        var err error

										

										
										

											144
											
                        payload, err = anypb.New(protoMsg)

										

										
										

											145
											
                        if err != nil {

										

										
										

											146
											
                                return fmt.Errorf("failed to serialize request: %w", err)

										

										
										

											147
											
                        }

										

										
										

											148
											
                } else {

										

										
										

											149
											
                        // For non-proto messages, serialize as JSON

										

										
										

											150
											
                        jsonData, err := json.Marshal(request)

										

										
										

											151
											
                        if err != nil {

										

										
										

											152
											
                                return fmt.Errorf("failed to serialize request as JSON: %w", err)

										

										
										

											153
											
                        }

										

										
										

											154
											
                        payload = &anypb.Any{

										

										
										

											155
											
                                TypeUrl: "application/json",

										

										
										

											156
											
                                Value:   jsonData,

										

										
										

											157
											
                        }

										

										
										

											158
											
                }

										

										
										

											159
											
        }

										

										
										

											160
											

										

										
										

											161
											
        // Create gRPC request

										

										
										

											162
											
        grpcReq := &rpcproto.RPCRequest{

										

										
										

											163
											
                Method:  method,

										

										
										

											164
											
                Payload: payload,

										

										
										

											165
											
        }

										

										
										

											166
											

										

										
										

											167
											
        // Make the call

										

										
										

											168
											
        grpcResp, err := client.Call(callCtx, grpcReq)

										

										
										

											169
											
        if err != nil {

										

										
										

											170
											
                return fmt.Errorf("gRPC call failed: %w", err)

										

										
										

											171
											
        }

										

										
										

											172
											

										

										
										

											173
											
        // Check for error in response

										

										
										

											174
											
        if grpcResp.Error != "" {

										

										
										

											175
											
                return fmt.Errorf("service error: %s", grpcResp.Error)

										

										
										

											176
											
        }

										

										
										

											177
											

										

										
										

											178
											
        // Convert response from Any

										

										
										

											179
											
        if response != nil && grpcResp.Result != nil {

										

										
										

											180
											
                if protoMsg, ok := response.(proto.Message); ok {

										

										
										

											181
											
                        if err := grpcResp.Result.UnmarshalTo(protoMsg); err != nil {

										

										
										

											182
											
                                return fmt.Errorf("failed to deserialize response: %w", err)

										

										
										

											183
											
                        }

										

										
										

											184
											
                } else {

										

										
										

											185
											
                        // For non-proto messages, deserialize from JSON

										

										
										

											186
											
                        if grpcResp.Result.TypeUrl == "application/json" {

										

										
										

											187
											
                                if err := json.Unmarshal(grpcResp.Result.Value, response); err != nil {

										

										
										

											188
											
                                        return fmt.Errorf("failed to deserialize response from JSON: %w", err)

										

										
										

											189
											
                                }

										

										
										

											190
											
                        } else {

										

										
										

											191
											
                                return fmt.Errorf("unsupported response type: %s", grpcResp.Result.TypeUrl)

										

										
										

											192
											
                        }

										

										
										

											193
											
                }

										

										
										

											194
											
        }

										

										
										

											195
											

										

										
										

											196
											
        return nil

										

										
										

											197
											
}

func (r *RedisRegistry) notifyWatchers(serviceName string, info rpc.ServiceInfo) {

										

										
										

											294
											
        r.watcherMu.RLock()

										

										
										

											295
											
        defer r.watcherMu.RUnlock()

										

										
										

											296
											

										

										
										

											297
											
        channels, exists := r.watchers[serviceName]

										

										
										

											298
											
        if !exists {

										

										
										

											299
											
                return

										

										
										

											300
											
        }

										

										
										

											301
											

										

										
										

											302
											
        for _, ch := range channels {

										

										
										

											303
											
                select {

										

										
										

											304
											
                case ch <- info:

										

										
										

											305
											
                default:

										

										
										

											306
											
                        r.logger.Warnf("Failed to notify watcher for service: %s", serviceName)

										

										
										

											307
											
                }

										

										
										

											308
											
        }

										

										
										

											309
											
}

											242
											
func (r *RedisRegistry) Close() error {

										

										
										

											243
											
        close(r.stopChan)

										

										
										

											244
											

										

										
										

											245
											
        // Close all watcher channels

										

										
										

											246
											
        r.watcherMu.Lock()

										

										
										

											247
											
        for serviceName, channels := range r.watchers {

										

										
										

											248
											
                for _, ch := range channels {

										

										
										

											249
											
                        close(ch)

										

										
										

											250
											
                }

										

										
										

											251
											
                delete(r.watchers, serviceName)

										

										
										

											252

func (r *RedisRegistry) Watch(ctx context.Context, name string) (<-chan rpc.ServiceInfo, error) {

										

										
										

											217
											
        r.watcherMu.Lock()

										

										
										

											218
											
        defer r.watcherMu.Unlock()

										

										
										

											219
											

										

										
										

											220
											
        // Create a new channel for this watcher

										

										
										

											221
											
        ch := make(chan rpc.ServiceInfo, r.config.WatchBufferSize)

										

										
										

											222
											

										

										
										

											223
											
        if r.watchers[name] == nil {

										

										
										

											224
											
                r.watchers[name] = make([]chan rpc.ServiceInfo, 0)

										

										
										

											225
											
        }

										

										
										

											226
											
        r.watchers[name] = append(r.watchers[name], ch)

										

										
										

											227
											

										

										
										

											228
											
        // Send initial state if service exists

										

										
										

											229
											
        if info, err := r.GetService(ctx, name); err == nil {

										

										
										

											230
											
                select {

										

										
										

											231
											
                case ch <- *info:

										

										
										

											232
											
                default:

										

										
										

											233
											
                        r.logger.Warnf("Failed to send initial state to watcher for service: %s", name)

										

										
										

											234
											
                }

										

										
										

											235
											
        }

										

										
										

											236
											

										

										
										

											237
											
        r.logger.Infof("Started watching service: %s", name)

										

										
										

											238
											
        return ch, nil

										

										
										

											239
											
}

func (r *RedisRegistry) GetService(ctx context.Context, name string) (*rpc.ServiceInfo, error) {

										

										
										

											150

											151
											

										

										
										

											152

											153

											154
											
                return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to get service from Redis: %w", err)

										

										
										

											155

											156
											

										

										
										

											157

											159

											160
											

										

										
										

											161
											
        var info rpc.ServiceInfo

										

										
										

											162

											163

											165
											
        }

										

										
										

											166
											

										

										
										

											167
											
        return &info, nil

										

										
										

											168

func (r *RedisRegistry) refreshServices() {

										

										
										

											328

											329

											330
											

										

										
										

											331

											332

											333

											336

											339

											340
											
                        err := r.Register(ctx, service)

										

										
										

											341

											342

											343

											344
											
                }

										

										
										

											345
											
        }

										

										
										

											346
											
}

											116
											

										

										
										

											117
											
        // Store in Redis with TTL

										

										
										

											118

func (r *RedisRegistry) ListServices(ctx context.Context) ([]rpc.ServiceInfo, error) {

										

										
										

											172

											173
											

										

										
										

											174

											176

											182

											183
											
                        return nil, fmt.Errorf("failed to scan Redis keys: %w", err)

											185

											188
											
                        if err != nil {

										

										
										

											189

											196
											

										

										
										

											197
											
                        var info rpc.ServiceInfo

											199

											200

        for k, v := range c.durationsSumNs {

										

										
										

											70
											
                dsum[k] = v

										

										
										

											71
											
        }

										

										
										

											72

											73

											199

											200

											201
											
                for i := len(s.interceptors) - 1; i >= 0; i-- {

										

										
										

											202

											203

											204
											
                return handler(ctx, req)

										

										
										

											205
											
        }

										

										
										

											206
											
}
